&#xa0;
[normal]Written evidence submitted by St Mungo’s[bold]St Mungo’s has been opening doors for homeless people since 1969. We currently run over 100 projects, providing accommodation for more than 1,700 people every night and helping thousands more who are rough sleeping or at risk of homelessness. St Mungo’s delivers a range of residential services from emergency shelters to semi-independent flats, as well as non-residential health, education and employment services. We also prevent homelessness through our housing advice programmes. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]St Mungo’s services are based on a recovery approach and we aim to work in partnership with clients in a personalised, effective way. Our clients often have complex problems that cause, or are caused by, homelessness; we deliver holistic support to help people rebuild their lives.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]1.1.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]L[bold]ocal housing allowance (LHA) caps combined [bold]with high demand for rental properties are likely to be making people homeless -[bold] There has been a 78 per cent increase the number of people becoming homeless due to the end of an assured shorthold tenancy, 
[normal]which is 
[normal]the most common type of private tenancy, 
[normal]when the first quarter of 2013 is compared to the first quarter of 2011.
